    dc:creator "Daniele, Scarponi; Landau, Bernard; Janssen, Ronald; Morgenroth, Holly; Bella, Giano Della" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Lectotype designation for Murex nebula Montagu 1803 (Mangeliidae) and its implications for Bela Leach in Gray 1847" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287444>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287443> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287444>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Optical microscope photos of teleoconch features; scale bars 1 mm. A – C) Bela fuscata (Deshayes, 1835) sensu Nordsieck (1977), from Punta Ala (Grosseto, Italy). D) Bela brachystoma (Philippi, 1844) from Djerba (Tunisia), and (F – G) from Porto Azzurro (Leghorn, Italy). G – I) † Bela hispidula (Bellardi, 1847) from Formello Quarry (Rome, Italy). J – L) Mangelia striolata Risso, 1826 from Procida Island (Naples, Italy). SEM photos of protoconch features; scale bar 0.1 mm. M) B. fuscata from Punta Pioppeto (Naples, Italy). N) B. brachystoma from Elba Island (Grosseto, Italy). O) † B. hispidula from Ca’ Lametta (Bologna, Italy). P) M. striolata from Djerba (Tunisia). Symbol: † fossil." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/287444/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.287443>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Optical microscope and scanning electron microscope (SEM) photos of Bela nebula (Montagu 1803); scale bars 1 mm and 0.1 mm, respectively. A – C lectotype, # Exem: Moll 4253 / 5; D – F topotype, # NMW 1953.183.02275 / 1; G – K topotype # NMW 1953.183.02276 / 1; L topotype # NMW 1953.183.02281 / 1. Topotype specimens from Torbay, Devon (UK). # shell number in Table 1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/287443/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

